datum.field:
[LaTeX]
The academic knowledge of the bodies of humans and common animals. The skill holder will know the location and function of various organs, muscles, etc. This skill is helpful for medical purposes, and to identify weaknesses of your foes.

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Misc/Vitruvian.jpg}

[LaTeX]

The scientific study of chemicals and chemical processes. A person with this skill will be able to identify chemicals and substances and make various chemical compounds (given the needed supplies, of course).

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Misc/The_Brewer_designed_and_engraved_in_the_Sixteenth_Century_by_J_Amman.png}

[LaTeX]
People with this skill have the ability to escape from bonds. This includes ropes, handcuffs, straight jackets, and similar restrictive bonds.

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Misc/HarryHoudini-1899.jpg}

[LaTeX]

Gathering information about something or someone using the media, interviewing people, looking at firsthand accounts and other evidence, etc.

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Misc/Holmes_by_Paget.jpg}

[LaTeX]

The skills of metalworking. This includes how to operate common tools in a metalworking shop, as well as processes such as welding, flame cutting, etc. A person with this skill can read blueprints, and can produce parts and devices from metal given the proper equipment. This skill is also useful for repairing mechanical devices, such as vehicles, robots, and mecha.

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Misc/Lathe.png}

[LaTeX]
The strategic deployment and command of troops, tanks, ships, and other units in war, police, security, and similar situations.
\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/MartialArts/Macedonian_Syntagma.jpg}

[LaTeX]

The academic study of natural laws, including mechanics, electricity and magnetism, optics, etc. The study of how and why things act the way they do.

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Misc/Roger_Bacon_optics01.jpg}

[LaTeX]
The art of working with metal with primitive techniques. Persons with this skill are experienced at forming metal with a forge, hammer, and anvil. This skill can be used to make simple tools, weapons, and other goods.
\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Misc/Scene-de-forge-edo.jpg}

[LaTeX]

A leather suit covered in overlapping and layerd metal plates that curve around the body.

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Equipment/Armor/Hirschvogel_Sigismund.jpg}

[LaTeX]
A thick, bulky vest that is padded and contains iron plates that cover vital areas of the chest and groin. (Millitary style, WWII, etc.)
\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Equipment/Armor/Sn-42b.jpg}

[LaTeX]

A fearsome sword with scalloped, flame-like, blade edges.  Sure to inspire terror in your enemies, before you cut them down where they stand.

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Equipment/Melee/Flamberge.png}

[LaTeX]

A 14'--18' flat stone (typically jade) paddle. Has a razor-sharp edge. Weighs about 4 pounds for a 14' version, and an addition pound per inch. For each additional pound/inch add +2 to the MSB.

\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/Equipment/Melee/Macahuitl.png}

[LaTeX]
You are trained to fight with two weapons simultaneously. Each skill level reduces the dual-wield penalty by 1 point for each hand. Note that no matter the level of Ambidexterity, it can never provide a positive bonus; it can only reduce or remove the normal penalty.
\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/MartialArts/two-weapon-style.png}
\quotexample[Candlestick is ambidextrous]{Candlestick has 3 levels of ambidexterity; he has -0 to strike with his `good' hand and -3 to strike with the off hand. If Candlestick had 6 levels of ambidexterity he would no negative at all when attacking with his 2$^{nd}$ weapon, and a -3 with his 3$^{rd}$ weapon, for instance if he were doing two punches and a kick.}

[LaTeX]
The skill of how to engage in ``gentlemanly,'' ``honorable'' or ``face-saving'' combat (duels, sport-combat, etc.). This includes battle-field code-of-conduct, rituals, battle-cries, cheers, negotation, the art of surrender etc. In any situation in which negotation must occur during the duress of combat, the \emph{Combat Etiquette} skill must be checked first. Without this skill it is \textit{impossible} in most cases to attempt to negotiate with the opposing party.
\VBoxColumnPicture{Images/MartialArts/Talhoffer_Thott_80r.jpg}
\quotexample[Br\H{a}tzefv negotiates peace]{In the dark Br\H{a}tzefv, bumped into some strangers and they began to fight, his gut-instinect tells him that this was just an accident and he wants to call out to his opponents that they should stop and talk. He rolls his \emph{Combat Etiquette} and has two successes; his opponents are not particularly eager to fight, and decide to stop and talk.}
\quotexample[Viterexia honorably slays her opponent]{Viterexia has just defeated the Warrior Mother of the Umex Clan in a single combat at the center of a stadium filled with 20,000 Umescis. Upon rolling \emph{Trivia} and \emph{Combat Etiquette} she realizes that she should cut off her opponents head, or the Warrior Mother will be forever disgraced and the Umescis will descend upon her and rip her to pieces. With a flourish and a cry she swings her Grand Sabre down and holds up the grizzly prize.}

[LaTeX]
For each level in \emph{Jitsu} pick one \textsc{Special} or one \textsc{Defensive} skill that the martial artist already knows. This special skill is now considered a \textsc{Basic} skill, and may be modified and used as a \textsc{Basic} skill.
\quotexample[Myk's Deadly Reciprocal Attack]{Myk is typically out-of-range of any opponent because he uses a Gladius, while Travis uses a 14' Yari. Most of the time, Myk focuses on defending himself and Travis using \emph{Defend Other}. However, because he has such fantastic armor (and gets hit a lot defending Travis), he really wants to be able to ``lay down the law'' with his \emph{Reciprocal Attack}. When he takes his 3$^{rd}$ level in Jitsu, he chooses \emph{Reciprocal Attack} as his skill; from now on Myk can modify \emph{Reciprocal Attack} as if it were a \textsc{Basic} attack; in particular he has 3 levels in \emph{Deadly} he plans to use$\ldots$}

[LaTeX]
For each level in \emph{Kata} choose a \textsc{Basic} attack, a \textsc{Modifier} for that Basic attack, and any 0- or 1-action Skill (any!). All three of these skills are performed \emph{as a skill action}. All three must be rolled independently, and succeed or fail on their own. Each combination is considered a \textsc{Special} attack.
\quotexample[Running a Polearm]{Travis is tired of having those damn spry Elves ``run'' his polearm, his original problem was penetrating their armor, but by purchasing his Legendy Yari and learning the \emph{Reciprocal Attack} \emph{Jitsu} he's been doing better. However, he's picked up a little magic, and would like to be able to \emph{Bash} his opponent to increase the damage he deals, following by a \emph{Blink} to get the hell out of the way. So he buys a level in \emph{Jitsu} and makes \emph{Reciprocal Attack} a \textsc{Basic} skill. He then choose \emph{Reciprocal Attack}, \emph{Bash}, and \emph{Blink} for the first level he buys in Kata.}

[LaTeX]
Pick any two \textsc{Basic} skills, this \emph{Waza} is considered a \textsc{Special} skill that is the combination of the two skills. This is similar to \emph{Kung Fu}. The total Rank of this skill is one less than the sum of the Ranks of the two \textsc{Basic} skills.
\quotexample[Ragnar's Bar Fights]{Ragnar finds himself in more barfights than he wants, and decides that (a) nothing says ``I'm serious'' more than a \emph{Barrel Charge} but (b) he'd rather throw a punch or two into the whole operation. As a result he picks up a new \emph{Waza} combining \emph{Barrel Charge} with a Rank 2 \emph{Punch/Kick} at 2 levels. This means the \emph{Waza} has $1+2-1=2$ Rank, and at level 2, would cost 6 C.P. Note that Ragnar cannot further \textsc{Modify} this skill because it is \textsc{Special}.}
